# Auto Review for NativeWind UI

When editing UI files in this scope:

- Automatically apply `nativewind-guidelines` during implementation/review.
- If file uses NativeWind patterns (`className`, token classes, variant maps), run `nativewind-reviewer` after edits.
- For major UI work, also run `accessibility-auditor` and `design-system-enforcer`.
- If the change is substantial, run `yg-quality-gate`.

## Review expectations

- Use `className` for static styles and `style` only for dynamic values.
- Prefer shared wrappers in `src/components/ui/*` before raw primitives.
- Use i18n keys for user-visible strings.
- Flag hardcoded token-replaceable hex colors as blockers.
